  "prompt": "How do I reschedule my appointment for passport because I put the wrong email?",
  "response": "To reschedule your passport appointment due to an incorrect email, follow these steps:\n\n1. Contact the official passport agency:\n- Call the National Passport Information Center\n- Visit their website (travel.state.gov)\n- Check your original confirmation for contact information\n\n2. Explain your situation:\n- Inform them about the incorrect email\n- Request to reschedule or update your appointment\n- Provide correct contact information\n\n3. Alternative options:\n- Online rescheduling (if available on the website)\n- In-person at a passport acceptance facility\n- Schedule a new appointment with the correct email\n\n4. Have these details ready:\n- Original appointment date and time\n- Reason for rescheduling\n- Correct email address\n- Personal identification information\n\nThe specific process may vary depending on your location and the passport agency's current procedures, so it's best to contact them directly for the most accurate guidance.",
